BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2026-03-21-1000-vmfa@rvafiguredrawing
DTSTAMP:20260308T124742Z
DTSTART:20260321T100000
DTEND:20260321T160000
SUMMARY:Figure Drawing [27]
LOCATION:VMFA Studio School\, 200 N Arthur Ashe Boulevard\, Richmond\, VA 23220
DESCRIPTION:Start by exploring a variety of drawings of the human form by other artists. Then with guidance from the instructor and working from a live model\, learn to create expressive portraits in charcoal and pencil. Prerequisites: basic drawing skills. Instructor: Amy Smith. 1 session.\\n\\nCost: Member $80\\n\\nRegister: https://www.vmfa.museum/classes/figure-drawing-27
URL:https://www.vmfa.museum/classes/figure-drawing-27
END:VEVENT
